erâs goal, if your reader &lt;i&gt;wants&lt;/i&gt; to see your character succeed, he or she will empathize with your main character. Your reader will become &lt;i&gt;emotionally bonded&lt;/i&gt; to the character.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;Think about when you have &lt;b&gt;NOT&lt;/b&gt;finished a book. Itâs likely you stopped caring about the character. Donât let that happen in your novel.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;What's your favourite quote about writing/for writers?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;Remember to ask yourself, âHow can I make things worse for my main character?â Vladimir Nabokov (&lt;em&gt;Lolita&lt;/em&gt;) once said: âThe writerâs job is to get the main character up a tree, and then once they are up there, throw rocks at them.â Itâs great advice. Really.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Times; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;What's the best thing about being a writer?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: Times; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;That would definitely be connecting with readers along my journey as an author. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c0"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;Iâm indebted to my readers, my teachers, fellow writers, bloggers, and book reviewersâeveryone whoâs been kind enough to hel