ww.laurenclarkbooks.com/blog&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;Amazon Author Page:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.amazon.com/Lauren-Clark/e/B00631IN3G/ref=ntt_athr_dp_pel_1" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;Lauren Clark&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: #333333; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Facebook:&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Lauren-Clark/235315706518284"&gt;Lauren Clark&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;Twitter:&amp;nbsp; @Laurenclark_bks&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.pinterest.com/laurenclarkbks/"&gt;Pinterest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5280308.Lauren_Clark"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5280308.Lauren_Clark"&gt;Goodreads&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="background: white; line-height: 12.0pt; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;Who is you favorite character in your book and why?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; color: #333333; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;Definitely, my main character, Searcy Roberts. (It may take you a bit to love her as much as I do, but stick with me hereâ¦.) When we first meet Searcy, she is a very spoiled Southern belle whoâs been pampered and polished to shine in Atlantaâs hottest social scenes. She has a personal shopper, a group of wealthy girlfriends, and a credit card with no limit. She spends her days shopping, going out to lunch, planning parties, and socializing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="background: white; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="background: white; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: #333333; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;What makes her so special is that even in the first chapter, we glimpse the real Searcy. She knows, deep down, that something is wrong, but canât bring herself to admit it. She projects a positive, upbeat attitude and tries to keep things status quo, because she doesnât believe she can live without her husband Alton.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="background: white; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="background: white; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin: 0cm;"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="color: #333333; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;Altonâs leaving upends Searcyâs life. At first, it appears that the impending divorce is the end of the world, but Searcyâs journey makes her into an entirely different personâsomeone caring, giving, empathetic, and truly loving. Best of all, she learns to rely on herself, forgives Alton, and finds true love.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;Why do you thi&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;nk readers are going to enjoy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;your book?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; color: #333333; font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;The message is about really knowing yourself and what makes you happy. Searcy, the main character, has spent her whole life running after a dreamâone that she thinks looks perfect to her friends and family. Unfortunately, sheâs desperately unhappy and is clinging to the belief that she can just ignore the loneliness she experiences and the problems in her marriage. The message is also about the strength women have when their entire world falls apart. Searcy choosesâafter some initial mopingâthat she will fix her life and make it better. Even when faced with seemingly insurmountable obstacles, Searcy learns that she is smart and can persevere.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri;"&gt;Who designed the cover?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;The fantastic Damonza. Check out his work at &lt;a href="http://www.damonza.com/"&gt;www.damonza.com&lt;/a&gt;. Put simply, he seems to get my concept for the cover, and manages to come up with great concepts in a day or two. Heâs designed four covers for me and Iâve never been anything less than impressed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="float: left; margin-right: 1em; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-DKcUHuQVAS4/VHOKU7ohRLI/AAAAAAAASLs/xq3iIVRiFxE/s1600/AuthorPic.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-DKcUHuQVAS4/VHOKU7ohRLI/AAAAAAAASLs/xq3iIVRiFxE/s1600/AuthorPic.jpg" height="320" width="263" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Lauren Clark&lt;span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri;"&gt;Who inspires you?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span class="c0"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;I adore Sophie Kinsella, JoJo Moyes, and Jennifer Weiner. I absorb&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;and study novels by John Irving, Anne Patchett, and Sue Monk Kidd. My other favorites include Pat Conroy, Barbara Kingsolver, Ian McEwan, Chris Bohjalian, and Janet Fitch.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri;"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri;"&gt;What is your work in progress? Tell us about it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;Iâm currently writing the sequel to &lt;i&gt;Dancing Naked in Dixie&lt;/i&gt;, which was my second novel. &lt;i&gt;Dixie&lt;/i&gt;tells the story of Julia Sullivan, a NYC travel writer sent to the Deep South to cover a story in Eufaula, Alabama. When she arrives, and begins her research, she gets much more than she bargained for when she discovers the cityâs historic district is in danger of being replaced with a condominium development. Julia ends up falling in love with the city and fights for the preservation of Eufaulaâs historic landmarks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri;"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;Who or what inspired you to become a writer? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri;"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;I spent 6 years in television news as a reporter and anchor first! In many ways, my literary career began with a microphone, a notepad, and 90 seconds to tell a story. It was really the emotion-soaked stories that inspired and ignited meâa familyâs reunion after a soldierâs return from a tour of duty, the international adoption of two Russian twins (a process that took years), dramatic rescues, and tales of people persevering under the most challenging of odds.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;When I left the TV biz and started my family, I had a whole host of ideas to write about. Itâs been a long journey, as thereâs a big learning curve in the transition from journalist to novelist, but itâs been worth every hour that Iâve put into it!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-DrkNgojpT5o/VHOKluCTdYI/AAAAAAAASL0/SKX6KlF0J0Y/s1600/NBTM_PieGirls_Banner.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"&gt;&lt;img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-DrkNgojpT5o/VHOKluCTdYI/AAAAAAAASL0/SKX6KlF0J0Y/s1600/NBTM_PieGirls_Banner.jpg" height="160" width="400" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: Times; mso-bidi-font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.jolinsdell.com/" title="Jo Linsdell"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;img alt="blogsignatureWA" src="http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8176/8030439972_551fda411e.jpg" height="120" width="500" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;script src="//s7.addthis.com/js/300/addthis_widget.js#pubid=xa-51adb6a4646b451d" type="text/javascript"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;document.doAT = function(cl) {         var myclass = new RegExp('hentry');         var myTitleContainer = new RegExp('post-title');         var myPostContent = new RegExp('post-footer');         var elem = this.getElementsByTagName('div');            var url;         var title = "";                  for (var i = 0; i &lt; elem.length; i++)         {             var classes = elem[i].className;             if (myclass.test(classes))             {                 var container = elem[i];              url = window.location.href;                               for (var b = 0; b &lt; container.childNodes.length; b++)                 {                     var item = container.childNodes[b].className;                     if (myTitleContainer.test(item))                     {                         var link = container.childNodes[b].getElementsByTagName('a');                         if (typeof(link[0]) != 'undefined')                         {                             var url = link[0].href;                             var title = link[0].innerHTML;                         }                      var singleq = new RegExp("'", 'g');                     var doubleq = new RegExp('"', 'g');                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             title = title.replace(singleq, ''', 'gi');                     title = title.replace(doubleq, '"', 'gi');                      }                     if (myPostContent.test(item))                     {                         var footer = container.childNodes[b];                     }                 }                  var n = document.createElement('div');                  var at = "&lt;div class='addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style ' addthis:title='"+title+"' addthis:url='"+encodeURI(url)+"'   &gt; &lt;a class='addthis_button_facebook_like' fb:like:layout='button_count'&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class='addthis_button_tweet'&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class='addthis_button_pinterest_pinit'&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class='addthis_counter addthis_pill_style'&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt;";                  n.innerHTML = at;                  container.insertBefore(n , footer);                }         }     return true; };  document.doAT('hentry'); &lt;/script&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-count="none" data-via="jolinsdell"&gt;Tweet&lt;/a&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

